The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Aug. 1: Hindustan Petroleum Corporation Ltd has suffered a loss of Rs 507.89 crore in the quarter ended June 30 compared with a net profit of Rs 247.30 crore during the corresponding period previous fiscal. However, total income (net of excise) has increased to Rs 15144.33 crore against Rs 13701.56 crore in the year-ago period, the Mumbai-based public sector undertaking today informed the Bombay Stock Exchange. 

 New Delhi, Aug. 1: The National Aluminium Company (Nalco) today increased the prices of various aluminium products by Rs 1,000 to Rs 1,500 per metric tonne primarily due to fluctuations in the international markets. After the upward revision, various products would now cost between Rs 1,01,400 to nearly Rs 1,02,900 per metric tonne.

 London, Aug. 1: Royal Dutch Shell and BASF announced today the completion of the sale of petrochemical joint venture Basell to Nell Acquisition, an affiliate of New York-based Access Industries for $5.7 billion, including debt. 

 Helsinki, Aug. 1: Nokia?s chairman and chief executive Jorma Ollila will step down from his post in June 2006. Ollila will be replaced by the head of Nokia?s mobile phone unit, Olli-Pekka Kallasvuo, the group announced today.

 Chennai, Aug. 1: The Company Law Board (CLB), Chennai, today said it found various irregularities and non-compliances by Pentamedia Graphics Ltd and asked the Centre to appoint two directors on its board for three years to take ?corrective steps?.

 New Delhi, Aug. 1: The Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority (IRDA) today directed insurers to strictly comply with third-party liability cover for motor insurance in the wake of complaints regarding some companies violating norms.

 Singapore, Aug. 1: Wipro Infotech plans to expand into Sri Lanka and Bangladesh to tap the growing telecom and banking markets.




